msgid ""
"When using the Quarkus Spring Web compatibility layer on top of the reactive stack (`quarkus-rest-jackson`),\n"
"you cannot inject servlet-based request and response types such as `jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest` or `jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse`.\n"
"These types are only available when using the Classic RESTEasy stack (quarkus-resteasy / quarkus-resteasy-jackson), which relies on the Servlet API provided by `quarkus-undertow` dependency."
msgstr "在基于响应式技术栈（ `quarkus-rest-jackson` ）使用 Quarkus Spring Web 兼容层时，无法注入基于 Servlet 的请求和响应类型，例如 `jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest` 或 `jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse` 。 这些类型仅在使用经典 RESTEasy 栈（quarkus-resteasy / quarkus-resteasy-jackson）时可用，该栈依赖于 `quarkus-undertow` 依赖项提供的 Servlet API。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "To provide a Spring-friendly experience while staying reactive, Quarkus allows you to inject the following types into your `@ExceptionHandler` methods:"
msgstr "为了在保持响应式特性的同时提供符合 Spring 规范的开发体验，Quarkus 允许您将以下类型注入到 `@ExceptionHandler` 方法中："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "io.vertx.core.http.HttpServerRequest"
msgstr "io.vertx.core.http.HttpServerRequest"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "io.vertx.core.http.HttpServerResponse"
msgstr "io.vertx.core.http.HttpServerResponse"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"These types give you direct access to the underlying Vert.x HTTP layer.\n"
"This allows you to manipulate the response (e.g. set headers, cookies, or status codes) or enrich the returned information using details from the request."
msgstr "这些类型可让您直接访问底层的 Vert.x HTTP 层。这使您能够操作响应（例如设置头部、Cookie 或状态码），或利用请求中的详细信息来丰富返回的信息。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "For example:"
msgstr "例如："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"**Warning:** This is potentially dangerous.\n"
"Users should only do this if they understand the reactive model, and are aware that writing directly to the response can bypass normal handling of status codes, headers, and serialization."
msgstr "*警告：* 此操作可能存在风险。用户只有在充分理解响应式模型，并清楚直接写入响应可能会绕过对状态码、头部和序列化的常规处理的情况下，才应执行此操作。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Important Technical Note"
msgstr "重要技术说明"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/spring-web.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Please note that the Spring support in Quarkus does not start a Spring Application Context nor are any Spring infrastructure classes run.\n"
"Spring classes and annotations are only used for reading metadata and / or are used as user code method return types or parameter types.\n"
"What that means for end users, is that adding arbitrary Spring libraries will not have any effect. Moreover, Spring infrastructure\n"
"classes (like `org.springframework.beans.factory.config.BeanPostProcessor` for example) will not be executed."
msgstr "请注意，Quarkus 中的 Spring 支持不会启动 Spring 应用上下文，也不会运行任何 Spring 基础架构类。Spring 类和注解仅用于读取元数据，以及/或作为用户代码中方法的返回类型或参数类型。 这对最终用户而言意味着，添加任意的 Spring 库都不会产生任何效果。此外，Spring 基础架构类（例如 `org.springframework.beans.factory.config.BeanPostProcessor` ）也不会被执行。"

